The space
room in a 2 bedroom near it all in the Mission District, including BART. Internet, parking if you want, $10/night. Within blocks of 20 great places, including the #1 burrito in the US of A at La Tacqueria. Within a mile of there are probably another 50, the Mission is pretty great for food, shopping, music and parks. I am a mellow host, pretty busy working professional, who can point you to lots of great walks, runs and bike rides around SF and Bay Area. You don't need a car to do a lot here. House is very bike/pedestrian friendly, I can show you lots of good walks and rides.

name: Loft-like Apt./Garden
description:
Located on 26th St. in wonderful Noe Valley, this beautifully large furnished open apartment (540 square feet) with separate street level entrance in a two unit building. We live in the upstairs unit. Four windows open onto the quiet rear of the house and a private entrance to a private beautifully landscaped garden.

The space
Located on 26th St. in wonderful Noe Valley, this beautifully large furnished open apartment (540 square feet) with separate street level entrance in a two unit building. We live in the upstairs unit. Four windows open onto the quiet rear of the house and a private entrance to a private beautifully landscaped garden.

The apt. has everything needed in a fully equipped modern kitchen - stainless steel appliances (GE refrigerator, & gas stove with oven, stainless steel sink & garbage disposal and Bosch dishwasher), caesarstone counter and maple cabinets.

neighborhood_overview: We love Noe Valley. It is a wonderful friendly upscale neighborhood. There is a terrific mix of people who live here, many commute to Silicon Valley via (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) busses that stop a few blocks away from our home. There are lots of charming stores and restaurants within walking distance and our location makes it easily accessible to all parts of San Francisco by public transportation. Noe Valley also has more dogs (pets) than any other part of San Francisco.
host_about: Arlene is originally from New York and grew up in the Bronx, and Leon is a third generation San Franciscan. We are both retired. Leon loves to ski and play tennis.  Arlene is involved in local community services (Neighborhood Community Court and San Francisco's Civil Grand Jury).We love to travel and have visited many interesting cultures and countries (i.e. China, India, Vietnam). We enjoy trying new restaurants and taking part in the culture that SF has to offer. We are outgoing and friendly, but respect our guests privacy. We love meeting new people from all over the world, and that is what makes our hosting so much fun.

description:
The space
Please come and enjoy our master bedroom suite with a private 1/2 bath, in an 1880's Victorian in sunny Noe Valley. Centrally located to Noe's shops and easy walking distance to Valencia corridor, Dolores Park and the Mission, along with public transportation a block away.

The guest suite is two rooms with a bay window in the bedroom (queen size bed) and a decorative fireplace in the sitting room; these are joined in the middle by a vanity with a sink and an enclosed toilet across from a large closet. The main bath is located off the kitchen and is equipped with an Ofuro tub and shower.

The neighborhood has a small town feel, while being a half hour to downtown (on public transportation) or an hour to Napa or Silicon Valleys (by car; traffic permitting). Yet, it is only a short walk to all the smaller dynamic locations for dining, arts and cultural events.

neighborhood_overview:
Pacific Heights is one of the nicest historic neighborhoods that is centrally located in San Francisco.
Walking distance to five grocery stores - three blocks to either Whole Foods (one the corner or California street and Franklin street) or Molly Stones (on California street, after you pass Fillmore street). To mor4 blocks to Trader Joeâ€™s and two Safewayâ€™s - I e south and one north from my home, 5 minutes drive. Also fun grocery Japanese supermarket - 3 blocks and another ethnic one - Woori, Korean market.

Itâ€™s a great place to hike and run. I usually run to the Bay and sometimes to the Golden Gate Bridge and back through Lyon Stairs. Very scenic route. There are lost of beautiful parks close to my home. The closest park is just a 1.5 blocks away - on Laguna and Sacramento street.

My home is located close to the famous Fillmore Street and an easy walk to Union Street. Both streets are a shopping heaven. Also there are many great restaurants walking distan
host_about:
I am a physician and I moved to USA 22 years ago. I love what San Francisco city and the Bay Area has to offer. I feel very lucky and privileged to live in a beautiful and safe area of San Francisco called Pacific Heights. 

I am an avid mountaineer/climber and I travel usually once a year, for a month - long expedition trip. That is usually when I open the calendar in AirBnB for my apartment, as well as (separately) for my garage. 

I would like to rent my beautiful home to someone reliable for all that time when I am gone. 

The things I can't live without are my family, friends, mountains, my amazing home, nature, meditation and any kind of physical activity daily. 

My favorite travel destinations - to many to mention. I feel amazing in high altitude mountains. 

I climbed all the highest mountains in the world called Seven Summits (including Mt.Everest), as well as skied to the South Pole.  Beside that, all my travels and expeditions left me with amazing memories. 

My favorite books - too many to list here as I  read a lot, but I love the most  "Master and Margarita" by Michail Bulhakov. There are many books in my home, so if you have time feel free to read something new. I switched now to ebooks or audiobooks, as it doesn't take any physical space. 

My favorite food is prepared with local and organic ingredients - check out many restaurants on Fillmore street - you will have so many to choose from, even after Pandemic years. I love sushi and the best sushi in the city is a walking distance from my home - check out Tataki restaurant (on California street/Divisadero street) - amazing and fresh! 
I also would encourage you to check â€œState Bird Provisionsâ€, but you would need a reservation. Itâ€™s a 7 -10 minutes walking distance from my home. Located on Fillmore street. 

I travel a lot for business - Marriott hotels, but for fun - I prefer staying in a tent or in a cool Airbnb place in different cities all over the world. 

My motto in life is to live largely, â€œon the edge of my comfort zone", hence climbing or polar expeditions, and now posting my home at Airbnb website. 

Throughout the process of renting my home I learn that my HOAâ€™s CC&Rs (Homeowners Rules) do not allow for any short term rentals and I can only rent it for a month or longer. 

My modern apartment is located on the top floor of the beautiful Victorian (freshly painted) building (originally from 1896). I have the best view of Japan Town and Twin Towers as well as complete privacy in my home. 

I love green plants and I have many in my home and at the balcony. Iâ€™ll be very grateful if you could please water it once a week ( just a little bit :) to keep it lush and green. 

So far, I had wonderful guests from all over the world for the last ten years. I am super grateful for all people I met through AirBnB. 

Please feel free to ask me any questions before you send a reservation. 

I look forward to meeting you in person and to host you in my home.
 
Thank you.

neighborhood_overview: The Mission District is San Franciscoâ€™s oldest neighborhood home to delicious restaurants and fun galleries. Walk the historic streets to see the largest concentration of murals in the city and hop in a taxi to explore the area's other top locations.
host_about:
My Motto; "Every Day is a Good Day!"

*As of February 27, 2022  I was fully vaccinated by way of the Pfizer all available vaccine and the two boosters available. I also contracted Covid 19 or a variant in May 2022 and fully recovered.

Something about me and my home; Iâ€™m gay, 64, single, very fit and energetic, very outgoing and easy going. I have always lived in California and have traveled the world extensively. I absolutely love San Francisco and even more being in the Mission District. Entrepreneurial spirited, at age twenty-one I started a business which fulfilled insurersâ€™ responsibilities for auto losses involving vandalism and retired from that adventure just shy of 36 years later.  I have been vegan for four years now and I have redirected my culinary skills towards all things plant, sugar-free, and fat-free based cuisine.  I enjoy practicing yoga at Love Story just around the corner.  I am also an avid bicyclist and use my bike as my primary mode of transport in the city.  I am attending  Community College SF working my way to a zoological degree. Life is good.

As for my home, the location and views are arguably the best the Mission District can offer. The private roof deck, a green oasis for the otherwise concrete jungle of a Mission Street residence. My place faces west so it's on the street side and is usually quite noisy from people, traffic and sirens. Thankfully the residence was constructed in 2008 and  built  quite soundproof. The bedrooms are well sized and comfortably appointed. The sun always seems to shine in the Mission District.

Finally, I love being an AirBnB host which allows me to share my good fortune, meet wonderful people and make new friends. 

I hope that you choose to stay. 

Mark
